attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a worm with multiple malicious capabilities. It performs network reconnaissance by scanning for open SMB ports (TCP/445) and enumerating network shares using WNet APIs. It attempts to spread by copying itself to discovered shares. The malware establishes persistence by copying itself to a new location, setting the hidden attribute, and creating auto-run registry keys. It employs privilege escalation by stealing the access token from the shell process (likely explorer.exe) using `DuplicateTokenEx`. It also has the ability to terminate other processes and communicates with a C2 server via HTTP POST requests.
